 GRONK (gronk) [popularized by the cartoon strip "B.C." by Johnny Hart, but
the word apparently predates that] v. 1. To clear the state of a wedged
device and restart it. More severe than "to frob" (q.v.). 2. To break. "The
teletype scanner was gronked, so we took the system down." 3. GRONKED: adj.
Of people, the condition of feeling very tired or sick. 4. GRONK OUT: v. To
cease functioning. Of people, to go home and go to sleep. "I guess I'll gronk
out now; see you all tomorrow."